President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Judy Gaynor, currently a co-founding Member of the Chicago Committee of Human Rights Watch and a Member of the Advisory Committee of the Children's Rights Division, will be appointed as a member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. Richard P. Herman, an educational consultant, will also be appointed as a member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. Robert Langer, the David H. Koch Institute Professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, will be appointed as a member of the President's Committee on the National Medal of Science. Wendy Wanderman, an entertainment professional specializing in the production and marketing of motion pictures, will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee on the Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. Thomas E. Wheeler, a Managing Director at Core Capital Partners and former CEO of the Cellular Telecommunications & Internet Association, will be appointed as a member of the President's Intelligence Advisory Board.